{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1523,"text":"This is a work in process,"},{"time":4457,"text":"based on some comments\nthat were made at TED two years ago"},{"time":9016,"text":"about the need for the storage of vaccine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12689,"text":"(Video): [On this planet"},{"time":14333,"text":"1.6 billion people"},{"time":16872,"text":"don't have access to electricity"},{"time":18861,"text":"refrigeration"},{"time":23020,"text":"or stored fuels"},{"time":26000,"text":"this is a problem"},{"time":29459,"text":"it impacts:"},{"time":32265,"text":"the spread of disease"},{"time":35511,"text":"the storage of food and medicine"},{"time":37343,"text":"and the quality of life."},{"time":41270,"text":"So here's the plan ...\ninexpensive refrigeration"},{"time":43559,"text":"that doesn't use electricity,\npropane, gas, kerosene or consumables"},{"time":48999,"text":"time for some thermodynamics"},{"time":51515,"text":"And the story of the Intermittent\nAbsorption Refrigerator]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":54261,"text":"Adam Grosser: So 29 years ago,\nI had this thermo teacher"},{"time":56911,"text":"who talked about absorption\nand refrigeration, one of those things"},{"time":60038,"text":"that stuck in my head, a lot\nlike the Stirling engine:"},{"time":62590,"text":"it was cool, but you didn't know\nwhat to do with it."},{"time":65065,"text":"It was invented in 1858,\nby this guy Ferdinand Carr√©,"},{"time":67639,"text":"but he couldn't actually build\nanything with it"},{"time":69928,"text":"because of the tools at the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71573,"text":"This crazy Canadian named Powel Crosley\ncommercialized this thing"},{"time":75837,"text":"called the IcyBall, in 1928."},{"time":77861,"text":"It was a really neat idea,\nand I'll get to why it didn't work,"},{"time":80926,"text":"but here's how it works."},{"time":82124,"text":"There's two spheres\nand they're separated in distance."},{"time":84724,"text":"One has a working fluid,\nwater and ammonia,"},{"time":87104,"text":"and the other is a condenser."},{"time":88716,"text":"You heat up one side, the hot side."},{"time":90705,"text":"The ammonia evaporates\nand it recondenses in the other side."},{"time":93748,"text":"You let it cool to room temperature,"},{"time":96310,"text":"and then, as the ammonia reevaporates\nand combines with the water"},{"time":99497,"text":"back on the erstwhile hot side,"},{"time":101124,"text":"it creates a powerful cooling effect."},{"time":103417,"text":"So it was a great idea\nthat didn't work at all."},{"time":105858,"text":"They blew up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107076,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108635,"text":"Because you're using ammonia,\nyou get hugely high pressures"},{"time":111446,"text":"if you heated them wrong;"},{"time":112737,"text":"it topped 400 psi."},{"time":114516,"text":"The ammonia was toxic,\nit sprayed everywhere."},{"time":116680,"text":"But it was kind of an interesting thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118876,"text":"So the great thing about 2006,"},{"time":121332,"text":"there's a lot of really great\ncomputational work you can do."},{"time":124211,"text":"So we got the whole thermodynamics\ndepartment at Stanford involved --"},{"time":128310,"text":"a lot of computational fluid dynamics."},{"time":130164,"text":"We proved that most of the ammonia\nrefrigeration tables are wrong."},{"time":134123,"text":"We found some nontoxic refrigerants"},{"time":136200,"text":"that worked at very low vapor pressures."},{"time":138802,"text":"We brought in a team from the UK --"},{"time":140515,"text":"a lot of great refrigeration people,\nit turns out, in the UK --"},{"time":143514,"text":"and built a test rig,\nand proved that, in fact,"},{"time":145818,"text":"we could make a low-pressure,\nnontoxic refrigerator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149085,"text":"So this is the way it works."},{"time":150457,"text":"You put it on a cooking fire."},{"time":151893,"text":"Most people have\ncooking fires in the world,"},{"time":154027,"text":"whether it's camel dung or wood."},{"time":155605,"text":"It heats up for about 30 minutes,\ncools for an hour."},{"time":159410,"text":"You put it into a container\nand it will refrigerate for 24 hours."},{"time":163113,"text":"It looks like this."},{"time":164359,"text":"This is the fifth prototype,\nit's not quite done."},{"time":167200,"text":"It weighs about eight pounds,\nand this is the way it works."},{"time":170208,"text":"You put it into a 15-liter vessel,\nabout three gallons,"},{"time":173814,"text":"and it'll cool it down\nto just above freezing --"},{"time":176310,"text":"three degrees above freezing --"},{"time":177812,"text":"for 24 hours in a 30 degree C environment."},{"time":180876,"text":"It's really cheap."},{"time":182087,"text":"We think we can build these\nin high volumes for about 25 dollars,"},{"time":185187,"text":"in low volumes for about 40 dollars."},{"time":186942,"text":"And we think we can make refrigeration\nsomething that everybody can have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190436,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191636,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}